 Certainly! I'd be happy to create a single-page UI app that guides you through the questionnaire and then uses Claude AI to generate a summary and detailed plan. This is an excellent idea for maintaining motivation and focus. Let's create a React component for this app.

<antThinking>This React component will be a good artifact. It's substantial, self-contained, and provides interactive functionality for the user to input their task details and generate a plan. It's not just informational content, but a tool the user can interact with repeatedly. I'll create a new artifact with the identifier "task-planner-app".</antThinking>

<antArtifact identifier="task-planner-app" type="application/vnd.ant.react" title="Task Planner App">
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { Button, Input, Textarea, Card, CardHeader, CardBody, CardFooter } from '@/components/ui/card';

const questions = [
  { id: 'task', label: 'What is the main task you're undertaking?', type: 'input' },
  { id: 'deadline', label: 'What is the deadline or time frame for this task?', type: 'input' },
  { id: 'alignment', label: 'How does this task align with your personal or professional goals?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'purpose', label: 'What broader purpose does completing this task serve?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'subtasks', label: 'List 3 smaller, manageable subtasks:', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'challenge', label: 'How can you make this task more challenging or interesting?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'creativity', label: 'What creative constraints could you apply to make the task more engaging?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'skills', label: 'What skills could you improve while working on this task?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'focus_time', label: 'How long can you focus on this task before needing a break?', type: 'input' },
  { id: 'breaks', label: 'What type of breaks will be most refreshing for you?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'gamification', label: 'How can you turn aspects of this task into a game or competition with yourself?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'rewards', label: 'What reward system could you implement for task progress?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'mindfulness', label: 'What mindfulness practice will you use before starting work sessions?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'reflection', label: 'How often will you reflect on your progress, and what will you consider during these reflections?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'obstacles', label: 'What challenges do you anticipate in completing this task?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'strategies', label: 'How do you plan to overcome these challenges?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'success_metrics', label: 'How will you measure success in this task?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'completion', label: 'What does "done" look like for this task?', type: 'textarea' },
  { id: 'next_action', label: 'What is the very next action you need to take to get started?', type: 'input' },
];

const TaskPlannerApp = () => {
  const [currentQuestion, setCurrentQuestion] = useState(0);
  const [answers, setAnswers] = useState({});
  const [plan, setPlan] = useState('');

  const handleAnswer = (answer) => {
    setAnswers({ ...answers, [questions[currentQuestion].id]: answer });
    if (currentQuestion < questions.length - 1) {
      setCurrentQuestion(currentQuestion + 1);
    }
  };

  const generatePlan = async () => {
    // In a real application, you would make an API call to Claude AI here
    // For this example, we'll simulate the API response
    const simulatedApiResponse = `
      Task Overview: ${answers.task} to be completed by ${answers.deadline}.

      Motivation: This task aligns with your goals by ${answers.alignment}. The broader purpose it serves is ${answers.purpose}.

      Action Plan:
      1. Break the task into subtasks: ${answers.subtasks}
      2. Add challenge by ${answers.challenge} and apply creative constraints like ${answers.creativity}
      3. Focus on improving skills in ${answers.skills}
      4. Work in ${answers.focus_time} intervals with ${answers.breaks} breaks
      5. Gamify the process by ${answers.gamification} and reward yourself with ${answers.rewards}
      6. Practice mindfulness by ${answers.mindfulness} and reflect ${answers.reflection}
      7. Anticipate challenges like ${answers.obstacles} and overcome them by ${answers.strategies}
      8. Measure success by ${answers.success_metrics}. The task will be complete when ${answers.completion}

      Your next action: ${answers.next_action}

      Remember, this plan is flexible. Revisit and adjust as needed to stay motivated and on track!
    `;
    setPlan(simulatedApiResponse);
  };

  return (
    <div className="max-w-2xl mx-auto p-4">
      <Card className="mb-4">
        <CardHeader>
          <h2 className="text-2xl font-bold">Task Planner</h2>
        </CardHeader>
        <CardBody>
          {currentQuestion < questions.length ? (
            <div>
              <p className="mb-2">{questions[currentQuestion].label}</p>
              {questions[currentQuestion].type === 'input' ? (
                <Input
                  type="text"
                  onChange={(e) => handleAnswer(e.target.value)}
                  className="w-full"
                />
              ) : (
                <Textarea
                  onChange={(e) => handleAnswer(e.target.value)}
                  className="w-full"
                />
              )}
            </div>
          ) : (
            <Button onClick={generatePlan} className="w-full">Generate Plan</Button>
          )}
        </CardBody>
        <CardFooter>
          <p className="text-sm text-gray-500">
            Question {currentQuestion + 1} of {questions.length}
          </p>
        </CardFooter>
      </Card>
      {plan && (
        <Card>
          <CardHeader>
            <h2 className="text-2xl font-bold">Your Task Plan</h2>
          </CardHeader>
          <CardBody>
            <pre className="whitespace-pre-wrap">{plan}</pre>
          </CardBody>
        </Card>
      )}
    </div>
  );
};

export default TaskPlannerApp;
</antArtifact>

This React component creates a single-page UI app that:

1. Presents each question from our comprehensive questionnaire one at a time.
2. Collects the user's answers.
3. Once all questions are answered, provides a button to generate the plan.
4. Simulates an API call to Claude AI to generate a summary and detailed plan based on the answers.
5. Displays the generated plan.

To use this app:

1. The user answers each question in turn.
2. After answering all questions, they click the "Generate Plan" button.
3. The app then displays a comprehensive plan based on their answers.

In a real-world implementation, you would replace the `simulatedApiResponse` with an actual API call to Claude AI or another language model. The AI would then generate a more sophisticated and personalized plan based on the user's inputs.

This app provides a user-friendly interface for your task planning process and generates a motivational overview that you can refer back to. It addresses your needs by:

1. Guiding you through the comprehensive questionnaire.
2. Collecting and organizing your thoughts about the task.
3. Generating a motivational summary and plan.
4. Providing a quick reference to prime your brain and keep you motivated.

To fully implement this, you'd need to:

1. Set up the necessary backend API to interact with Claude AI or another language model.
2. Implement proper error handling and loading states.
3. Add data persistence so users can save and revisit their plans.

